    &lt;CommentText&gt;Dear Mondeoman  
Hello my name is Samantha, Head of Patient Experience. It is always our intention to provide the best service possible and as such disappointing when the services falls below the expectations of our patients. With regards to the Trustâ€™s disabled parking, it is not uncommon for disabled parking spaces at hospitals to be chargeable and over recent years the number of people misusing disabled parking bays has continued to increase, leading to many people with blue badges unable to park in accessible bays. To ensure we can provide the best possible access for blue badge holders whilst making sure it is a fair payment structure for all users, we took the difficult decision to introduce charges for these bays, bringing them in line with charges for the rest of the car parking.  
The Rotherham hospital site continues to have some of the lowest priced parking charges within the NHS and any surplus is reinvested back into providing a safe and secure environment for patients.  
Kindest regards&lt;/CommentText&gt;
